{"id":7579,"date":"2017-10-21T06:40:57","date_gmt":"2017-10-21T13:40:57","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=7579"},"modified":"2024-01-08T17:49:17","modified_gmt":"2024-01-09T01:49:17","slug":"carlyle-creek-trail","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/10\/21\/carlyle-creek-trail\/","title":{"rendered":"CARLYLE CREEK TRAIL"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Located just north of Kokanee Glacier Provincial Park in the Keen Creek drainage, this hike takes you into Flint Lakes and the alpine ridges around Mt Carlyle. Unfortunately, most of the hike is along a washed-out, dusty mining road.<\/em>\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Rating: \u2666\u25ca\u25ca\u25ca\u25ca<br \/>\nDifficulty:<\/strong>\u00a0D2 strenuous\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation gain:<\/strong> 1067m (3500&#8242;)<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Key elevations:<\/strong> Bridge over Keen Ck 3200&#8242;; Lower Flint Lake 6150&#8242;<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 6.4km<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 4 hours one-way<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> mid-June to October<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Difficult<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/14 Slocan<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive<\/strong>:\u00a0<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Keen Creek Rd<\/span>. Closed at km 15.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> From New Denver: Drive east on Hwy 31A\u00a040.1 km (24.9 miles). Zero odometer.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> From Kaslo (Junction of\u00a0Highways 31 and 31A): Drive northwest 6.5 km (4 miles).\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> <strong>0.0<\/strong> Highway 31A.\u00a0Start southwest on gravel Keen Creek Road.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> 4.6km Nashton Road (left), just before km 5 sign.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> 6.5km Old road goes right, down; (to Mt. Carlyle, Flint Lakes). Park. Trailhead.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> Park at the creek. Cross Keen Creek. Hike 6.4 kilometres up the road to its terminus in the Flint Lakes Basin. The upper lakes are 600 and 1,000 feet above the lowest lake. From here the surrounding terrain can be explored.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>What to do?<br \/>\n<\/strong>1. Climb ridges around the lakes. Explore old mine ruins.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">2. Climb Mt Carlyle 8688&#8242; by the east ridge.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Located just north of Kokanee Glacier Provincial Park in the Keen Creek drainage, this hike takes you into Flint Lakes and the alpine ridges around Mt Carlyle. Unfortunately, most of the hike is along a washed-out, dusty mining road.\u00a0 Rating: &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/10\/21\/carlyle-creek-trail\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_stat